8 CHANGE CASH BALANCE REQUIREMENT TO CASH ON HAND
9 SECTION 3. G.S. 143C-6-11 reads as rewritten:
10 "§ 143C-6-11. Highway appropriation.
11 …
12 (f) Seven and One Half Percent (7.5%) Cash Balance Required. – The Department of
13 Transportation shall maintain an available cash balance at the end of each month to an amount
14 equal to at least seven and one half percent (7.5%) a minimum of 45 days of the total
15 appropriations for the current fiscal year from the Highway Fund and the Highway Trust Fund.
16 In projecting cash balances in future years, the Department shall use the estimated cash flow as
17 specified in the Current Operations Appropriation Act. No further transportation project contract
18 commitment may be entered into that would cause the cash position to fall below this
19 requirement. In the event this cash position is not maintained, no further transportation project
20 contract commitments may be entered into until the cash balance has been regained. Provided
21 the Department may modify or supplement transportation contract commitments for existing
22 transportation projects that (i) result in a savings from the total estimated project cost of the
23 existing commitment, based on a cost-savings analysis, or (ii) relate to the needs of an existing
24 transportation project to continue. Any federal funds on hand shall not be considered as cash for
25 the purposes of this subsection.
26 …
27 (k) The Department of Transportation shall do all of the following:
28 (1) Utilize cash flow financing to the extent possible to fund transportation
29 projects with the goal of reducing the combined average daily cash balance of
30 the Highway Fund and the Highway Trust Fund to an amount equal to between
31 fifteen and twenty percent (15-20%) 75 and 120 days of the total
32 appropriations for the current fiscal year from those funds. In projecting cash
33 balances in future years, the Department shall use the estimated cash flow as
34 specified in the Current Operations Appropriation Act. Any federal funds on
35 hand shall not be considered as cash for the purposes of this subsection. The
36 target amount shall include an amount necessary to make all municipal-aid
37 funding requirements of the Department.
38 …."
