40 ELIMINATE TURNPIKE AUTHORITY REPORTING REQUIREMENTS
41 SECTION 4. G.S. 136-89.193 reads as rewritten:
42 "§ 136-89.193. Annual plan of work; annual and quarterly reports.report.
43 (a) Annual Plan of Work. – The Authority shall annually develop a plan of work for the
44 fiscal year, describing the activities and projects to be undertaken, accompanied by a budget.
45 This annual plan of work shall be subject to the concurrence of the Board of Transportation.
46 (b) Annual Reports. Report. – The Authority shall, promptly following the close of each
47 fiscal year, submit an annual report of its activities for the preceding fiscal year and an annual
48 audit of its books and accounts for the preceding fiscal year to the Governor, the General
49 Assembly, and the Department of Transportation. The report and audit shall be submitted no later
50 than October 31 of the fiscal year in which the report and audit are completed.
