12 TURNPIKE UNPAID TOLL NOTICE BY ELECTRONIC MAIL
13 SECTION 5. G.S. 136-89.214(a) reads as rewritten:
14 "(a) Bill. – If a motor vehicle travels on a Turnpike project that uses an open road tolling
15 system and a toll for traveling on the project is not paid prior to travel or at the time of travel, the
16 Authority must send a bill by first-class mail to the registered owner of the motor vehicle or the
17 person who had care, custody, and control of the vehicle as established under G.S. 136-89.212(b)
18 for the amount of the unpaid toll; provided, however, that with the written consent of the
19 registered owner of the motor vehicle or the person who had care, custody, and control of the
20 vehicle as set forth above, the Authority may send the bill via electronic mail to a designated
21 electronic mail account or electronic mail account on file with any state Department of Motor
22 Vehicles rather than by first-class mail. The Authority must send the bill within 90 days after the
23 travel occurs, or within 90 days of receipt of a sworn affidavit submitted under
24 G.S. 136-89.212(b) identifying the person who had care, custody, and control of the motor
25 vehicle. If a bill is not sent within the required time, the Authority waives collection of the toll.
26 The Authority must establish a billing period for unpaid open road tolls that is no shorter than 15
27 days. A bill for a billing period must include all unpaid tolls incurred by the same person during
28 the billing period."
29
