13 CLARIFY USE OF REVENUE FROM TURNPIKE PROJECTS
14 SECTION 7. G.S. 136-89.188(a) reads as rewritten:
15 "(a) Revenues derived from a Turnpike Project authorized under this Article shall be used
16 only for the following costs associated with the Project from which the revenue was derived or a
17 planned contiguous toll facility:facility identified in a transportation plan adopted by an affected
18 Metropolitan Planning Organization:
19 (1) Authority administration costs.
20 (2) Development, right-of-way acquisition, design, construction, expansion,
21 operation, maintenance, reconstruction, rehabilitation, and replacement costs.
22 (3) Debt service on the Authority's revenue bonds or related purposes such as the
23 establishment of debt service reserve funds.
24 (4) Debt service, debt service reserve funds, and other financing costs related to
25 any of the following:
26 a. A financing undertaken by a private entity under a partnership
27 agreement with the entity for the Project.
28 b. Private activity bonds issued under law related to the Project.
29 c. Any federal or State loan, line of credit, or loan guarantee relating to
30 the Project.
31 (5) A return on investment of any private entity under a partnership agreement
32 with the entity for the Project.
33 (6) Any other uses granted to a private entity under a partnership agreement with
34 the entity for the Project."
