26 in the results of the criminal history check, provided all of the following conditions are satisfied:
27 (1) The previous criminal history check was conducted no more than three years
28 prior to the date of the request under this subsection.
29 (2) The individual who is the subject of the criminal history check has provided
30 written consent for the release of information on a form provided by the State
31 Bureau of Investigation that includes language that authorizes the disclosure
32 of criminal history results between local school boards for the purpose of
33 complying with employment or contracting requirements in a public school
34 unit.
35 (3) The local board of education requesting the results of the criminal history
36 check under this subsection submits its request using a form provided by the
37 State Bureau of Investigation that identifies the individual who is the subject
38 of the criminal history check and confirms that the information is being sought
39 for the purpose of meeting employment or contracting requirements in a
40 public school unit."
